value.value: This gene is involved in immunity and antigen recognition.

Human IGKV1-5 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 2p11.2 and is approximately 1 kb in length. This allele, which encodes immunoglobulin kappa variable 1-5 protein, plays a role in antigen binding and recognition.
Immunoglobulin kappa variable 1-5 (117 aa, ~13 kDa) is encoded by the human IGKV1-5 gene. This protein is involved in antigen binding by immunoglobulin light chains.
A change in the sequence of the H3-3B gene.
This gene may play a role in transcriptional regulation, osteoblast differentiation and matrix mineralization.

Human ZNF717 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 3p12.3 and is approximately 107 kb in length. This allele, which encodes zinc finger protein 717, may be involved in osteoblast differentiation, matrix mineralization and transcriptional regulation.
Zinc finger protein 717 (904 aa, ~105 kDa) is encoded by the human ZNF717 gene. This protein may play a role in transcriptional regulation during osteoblast differentiation and matrix mineralization.

This gene is involved in the ubiquitination and subsequent proteasomal degradation of induced myeloid leukemia cell differentiation protein Mcl-1, cellular tumor antigen p53, core histone proteins and DNA polymerase beta.
Caspase-8 (479 aa, ~55 kDa) is encoded by the human CASP8 gene. This protein plays a role in proteolysis, angiogenesis and caspase-induction of apoptosis.

Human HUWE1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of Xp11.22 and is approximately 155 kb in length. This allele, which encodes E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase HUWE1 protein, plays a role in the ubiquitination and proteasomal degradation of target proteins involved in apoptosis, tumor suppression, chromatin remodeling and DNA replication and repair. Mutations in the gene are associated with Turner type X-linked syndromic cognitive disability.

E3 ubiquitin-protein ligase HUWE1 (4374 aa, ~482 kDa) is encoded by the human HUWE1 gene. This protein is involved in the modulation of ubiquitination of target proteins involved in DNA replication and repair, apoptosis, chromatin remodeling, circadian rhythms and tumor suppression.

A nucleotide substitution at position 103 of the coding sequence of the H3-3A gene where guanine has been mutated to adenine.

A nucleotide substitution at position 104 of the coding sequence of the H3-3A gene where guanine has been mutated to thymine.
A nucleotide substitution at position 104 of the coding sequence of the H3-3B gene where guanine has been mutated to thymine.
Serine/threonine-protein kinase STK11 (433 aa, ~49 kDa) is encoded by the human STK11 gene. This protein plays a role in signal transduction and apoptosis.
A change in the amino acid residue at position 35 in histone H3.3 protein where glycine has been replaced by valine.
A nucleotide substitution at position 103 of the coding sequence of the H3-3A gene where guanine has been mutated to thymine.

A change in the amino acid residue at position 35 in histone H3.3 protein where glycine has been replaced by tryptophan.
This gene plays a role in lung function and alveolar homeostasis.

Human SFTPB wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 2p11.2 and is approximately 11 kb in length. This allele, which encodes pulmonary surfactant-associated protein B, is involved in respiratory airway homeostasis. Mutations in the gene are associated with pulmonary surfactant metabolism dysfunction type 1 (pulmonary alveolar proteinosis due to surfactant protein B deficiency).
Pulmonary surfactant-associated protein B (381 aa, ~42 kDa) is encoded by the human SFTPB gene. This protein plays a role in alveolar stability.

label.value: Ann Arbor A vs B Staging Designation

value.value: An indication whether A- or B-designations, based on the Ann Arbor lymphoma classification system guidelines, were used to modify staging classifications.

label.value: Histone Acetyltransferase Type B Catalytic Subunit

value.value: Histone acetyltransferase type B catalytic subunit (419 aa, ~50 kDa) is encoded by the human HAT1 gene. This protein plays a role in both histone acetylation and chromatin silencing.

TATA-binding protein-associated factor 172 (1849 aa, ~207 kDa) is encoded by the human BTAF1 gene. This protein is involved in transcriptional regulation.
